Governor Bala Mohammed of Bauchi State has declared that his Benue State counterpart, Samuel Ortom is the most outspoken governor against the maladministration of the President Muhammadu Bu­hari-led All Progressives Con­gress (APC) administration. Bala Mohammed, who made the declaration when he visited Governor Ortom at Government House, Makurdi on Friday also stated that as far as he was concerned, there was no government and no gover­nance in Nigeria. The Bauchi State governor, who is also a Presidential aspi­rant on the platform of the Peo­ple’s Democratic Party (PDP) was in the state to woo delegates of the party ahead of the PDP primaries. -Advertisement- Mohammed who point­ed out that Governor Ortom was a patriot said he intends to join hands with his Benue State counterpart to rescue the nation from the maladminis­tration of the APC-led govern­ment.